         "people": [
            {
               "id": "2405ace1-a0d5-4807-aacb-99e00587e7dd",
               "name": "Girnamme",
               "surname": "",
               "patronymic": "",
               "fullname": "Girnamme",
               "sex": "male",
               "gender": "male",
               "is_real": true,
               "haplogroup": null,
               "history": [
                  {
                     "text": "The conclusions about the period in which he lived and, consequently, about the total number of kings who ruled — in the works we are studying — are divergent.\n\n#### An initial view\n\nWalther Hinz proposes that the first mention of his name occurred in <htdate0>, indicating that his presence in a list of 12 kings of Susa would be incorrect (<htcite0>). Still in his work, it is mentioned that *\"Shu-Sin married one of his daughters to the ‘Prince of Anshan\"*, it being impossible to determine precisely whether it is a reference to Girnamme or to a vassal (<htcite1>).\n\nThe mention of Anshan leads us to an event that would occur more than a millennium later and that deserves a reflection (<htcite2>):",
                     "source": [
                        {
                           "type": 1,
                           "uuid": "c1a3a583-2fdd-4128-ac2e-fef02c089b04",
                           "text": "Hinz, W.",
                           "page": "pp. 81",
                           "date_time": {
