                     "PostMention": ""
                  },
                  {
                     "text": "An analysis of the work of Walther Hinz (<htcite0>) shows that the supposed list mentioned in the reflection does not exist. Furthermore, with the current knowledge about Elam, it is not possible to trace a continuous history with the necessary details to identify all of Cyrus's ancestors in that time interval, even though he dominated an extensive empire for his time.\n\n#### The other side\n\nWhen analyzing the work of Hamidreza Qashqai, we find another proposal. According to him, King Girnamme would have lived around <htdate0> and, in that period, would have obtained dominion over Anshan and Shimashki, which would justify the appearance of his name in the list of kings of Awan (<htcite1>).",
                     "source": [
                        {
